From a92464e6eafa68683253c43280eb2915876fb3a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:29:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 24/39] WIP: media: dvb-frontends: cxd2878: fix operator
 precedence in register status checks

In cxd2878_atsc_SlaveRWriteRegister() and cxd2878_atsc_softreset() the
expression "rdata[0]&0x3F!=0x30" is parsed as "rdata[0] & (0x3F != 0x30)"
because != has higher precedence than &, reducing the test to
"rdata[0] & 1". Add parentheses so the masked value is compared against
0x30 as intended, which also fixes the -Wparentheses warnings.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c
index 99229abd05b3..fb424fc3334c 100644
--- a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c
+++ b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c
@@ -352,7 +352,7 @@ static int cxd2878_atsc_SlaveRWriteRegister (struct cxd2878_dev*dev,
 			ret = -1;
 			goto err;}
 	  }
-   	if(rdata[0]&0x3F!=0x30){
+   	if((rdata[0]&0x3F)!=0x30){
 		ret = -1;
 		goto err;
    	}
@@ -425,7 +425,7 @@ static int cxd2878_atsc_softreset(struct cxd2878_dev *dev)
 			goto err;}
 	  }	
 
-	 if(rdata[0]&0x3F!=0x30){
+	 if((rdata[0]&0x3F)!=0x30){
 		ret = -1;
 		goto err;
    	 }
